  "text": "During a program to identify MTX poly(g-glutamate) synthesis modulators in CCRF-CEM cells, we found that AICAr enhances accumulation of these cytotoxic metabolites up to 3-fold during a 4-hour incubation (Table 1) . AICAr causes a rapid increase in MTX influx (Fig. 2) that is also %3-fold, suggesting that increased metabolite accumulation at 4 hours results from increased substrate availability for polyglutamylation. We evaluated AICAr because MTX polyglutamate accumulation presents a folate stress and Bochner and Ames [CITATION_1] showed that AICAr triphosphate (or related metabolites) regulates folate metabolism during folate stress.",
